claim.claim-text:
11. A method of switching from a first optical fiber to a second optical fiber, comprising:
receiving, at a first input of a large scale switching component, an optical signal from the first optical fiber;
outputting the optical signal via a first output of the large scale switching component to a working fiber input of a small scale switching component;
outputting the optical signal via a small scale output of the small scale switching component;
establishing, by a controller, an optical cross connect in the large scale switching component between a second input coupled to the second optical fiber and a second output coupled to a backup fiber input of the small scale switching component;
receiving a second optical signal from the second optical fiber at the second input of the large scale switching component;
switching the small scale switching component from the working fiber input to the backup fiber input upon receipt of the second optical signal at the second input of a large scale switching component; and
outputting the second optical signal via the small scale output of the small scale switching component.
